Consider a random walk with three possible states and where the random
walker (possibly) changes from state to state once every day according
to the transition matrix \emph{P}. Answer the following questions using
the martix \emph{P} and some of its powers given below.

\begin{align*}
P = \begin{bmatrix} 0.0284 & 0.5938 & 0.1626 \\ 0.9207 & 0.1579 & 0.1634 \\ 0.0509 & 0.2483 & 0.6740 \end{bmatrix}
\\
P^{10} = \begin{bmatrix} 0.2832 & 0.2907 & 0.2875 \\ 0.3843 & 0.3753 & 0.3786 \\ 0.3325 & 0.3340 & 0.3339 \end{bmatrix}
\\
